        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 3:10PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 310 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Schriever Space Force Base, or 14 miles east of Colorado Springs,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southeastern Colorado Springs, Fountain, Hanover, Schriever Space
Force Base, and Security-Widefield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM MDT for
east central Colorado.</instruction>
